/************************************************************************/
/**********      BEGINNING: GETTING A QQplot        *********************/
/************************************************************************/

title "Figure 1: QQ Plot";
proc univariate data=work.myeloma_clean normaltest plots; 
VAR MCHC;
run;
title;

/* Normality Discussion:
There is random jiggle around the agreement line with normality AND the p-values 
(.0005, .0100, .0050, .0050) are all greater than .05. Conclusion is that the x-values 
are normal enough to use a parametric procedure to analyze the center against 34 grams per deciliter. */
/************************************************************************/
/**************  END: GETTING QQ PLOTS   ********************************/
/************************************************************************/

/************************************************************************/
/*********  BEGINNING: ONE MEAN T TEST   *************/
/************************************************************************/

/*A One Mean t Test will have the most power to detect if the center is different from 34 grams per deciliter.*/

ods graphics on/ outputfmt=static;
title1 h=12pt "Is the average MCHC level lower than the";
title2 h=12pt "normal average of 34 grams per deciliter?";
Proc ttest data=work.myeloma_clean plots=none sides=L H0=34 alpha=0.05;
var MCHC; 
run;
title;
ods graphics off;

/* Hypotheses:
	H_0: μ=34	The true average MCHC level for multiple myeloma patients is 34 gram per deciliter.  
	H_a: μ<34 	The true average MCHC level for multiple myeloma patients is less than 34 grams per deciliter.
	
Significance Level (α = 0.05):
There is a 5% chance that I will conclude the true MCHC level for multiple myeloma patients is less than 34 grams 
per deciliter when the true MCHC Level for multiple myeloma patients is 34 gram per deciliter.*/
/************************************************************************/
/*********  END: ONE MEAN T TEST   *************/
/************************************************************************/


/************************************************************************/
/*********  BEGINNING: POST HOC PROCEDURE   *************/
/************************************************************************/
ods graphics on/ outputfmt=svg;
title1 h=10pt "Confidence Interval for the True MCHC Level of Algerian Patients with Myeloma";
title2 h=9pt "n = 198";
PROC MEANS Data=work.myeloma_clean n mean median stddev clm alpha=0.05 maxdec=4;
Var MCHC; 
run;
title;
ods graphics off;

/* We are 95% confident that the true MCHC level for all multiple myeloma patients is between 32.9358 
	grams per deciliter and 33.4557 grams per deciliter. The hypothesized MCHC level of 34 grams per deciliter 
	does not lie within this interval which agrees with our conclusion to reject the null hypothesis that the 
	true mean is equal to 34 grams per deciliter. */
/************************************************************************/
/*********  END: POST HOC PROCEDURE   *************/
/************************************************************************/


